0029|- [HelpText]
0030|*PLAY SOUND <pathname of a sound file>
S   |            <                        >
0031|*plays back synchronously a given sound file.
0032|*PLAY SOUND <sound file>,<max.time>
S   |            <          > <        >
0033|*plays back asynchronously a given sound file using max.time (in millisec.)
0034|*PLAY SOUNDS
0035|*sound_file_1
0036|*sound_file_2
0037|*...
0038|*plays back synchronously a series of sound files.
0039|*Default directory of Survo sound files is <Survo>\U\SND .
S   |                                           <     >
0040|*Default type of a sound file is .WAV. In playback Survo is using
0041|*the WIN32 API function PlaySound().
0042|*Ready-made sound files (.WAV) in your PC can be found, for example, by
0043|*WHERE C:\*.WAV
0044|*Examples:
0045|*PLAY SOUND Fringilla.coelebs
0046|*PLAY SOUNDS
0047|*Cuculus.canorus
0048|*Cuculus.canorus
0049|*Fringilla.coelebs
