0056|- [HelpText]
0057|*Creating sound files from Survo data
0059|*There are two alternatives for making sounds based on Survo data.
0061|*1. Sounds from raw data:
0062|*Consecutive values of one (mono) or two (stereo) variables in a Survo
0063|*sound files can be saved as such in a WAV file by PLAY DATA command
0064|*and played back by PLAY SOUND commmand.
0066|*2. Mapping data values to given sounds:
0067|*Consecutive values of selected variables in Survo data files can be
0068|*replaced by sounds and "played" by
0069|*PLAY DATA <data> / VOICES=<list of given voices>.
S   |           <    >          <                    >
0071|*Description of these alternatives not yet ready!
0072|*Examples (in Finnish) by
0073|*/LOAD <Survo>\U\SND\PLAYDATA
S   |       <     >
