0109|- [HelpText]
0110|*Sound files from raw data
0112|*PLAY DATA <Survo_data>,<variable>
S   |           <          > <        >
0113|*moves the values of <variable> in <Survo_data> in a sound file
S   |                     <        >    <          >
0114|*given by a WAV specification.
0115|*The default format of the WAV file is 16 bit mono with 11025 Hz
0116|*sample rate.
0117|*Values of <variable> must be in the interval [-32767,32767].
S   |           <        >
0119|*Example 1:
0120|*s(X):=sin(X*ORDER)
0121|*FILE MAKE DAT,1,24000,X,2
0122|*VAR X=8000*(s(0.2)+s(0.25)+s(0.3)) TO DAT / Pure major triad
0123|*PLAY DATA DAT,X  / WAV=MAJOR  Making file MAJOR.WAV from X in DAT
0124|*PLAY SOUND MAJOR / Playback of MAJOR
0125|*VAR X=8000*(s(0.2)+s(0.2*6/5)+s(0.3)) TO DAT / Pure minor triad
0126|*PLAY DATA DAT,X  / WAV=MINOR
0127|*PLAY SOUND MINOR / Playback of MINOR
0128|E
0129|*................................................................................
0130|*Example 2:
0131|*s(X):=sin(X*ORDER)
0132|*FILE MAKE DAT,1,36000,X,2
0133|*VAR X=8000*(s(0.2)+s(0.2*k)+s(0.3)) TO DAT
0134|*k=if(ORDER<4001)then(6/5)else(k2)
S   |           <
0135|*k2=if(ORDER>28000)then(5/4)else(k3)
S   |            >
0136|*k3=6/5+(5/4-6/5)/23999*(ORDER-4000)
0137|*PLAY DATA DAT,X / WAV=MM
0138|*PLAY SOUND MM
0139|*FILE SHOW DAT
0140|*................................................................................
0143|*GPLOT DAT,TIME,k
0144|*LINE=1
0145|*$E
